# ACloudViewer Agent Integration Development Rules

## JSON-RPC Plugin (C++)

- All new RPC methods MUST be added to:
  1. The dispatch table in `JsonRPCPlugin::execute()` in `JsonRPCPlugin.cpp`
  2. Method declarations in `JsonRPCPlugin.h`
  3. The `rpcMethodsList()` introspection method
- Method naming convention: `category.action` (e.g., `cloud.computeNormals`, `view.screenshot`)
- All methods MUST return `JsonRPCResult::success(...)` or `JsonRPCResult::error(code, message)`
- Entity lookups use `findEntityById(m_app->dbRootObject(), entityId)`
- After visual changes, always call `redraw()` to update the viewport
- Use `ecvMainAppInterface` methods for app interaction, not direct MainWindow access
- The WebSocket server listens on port 6001 by default

## MCP Server (Python)

- MCP tools are defined in `acloudviewer/agent-harness/cli_anything/acloudviewer/mcp_server.py`
- Each tool needs: a `Tool()` definition in `list_tools()` AND a handler in `call_tool()`
- The backend (`ACloudViewerBackend`) supports dual mode: GUI (RPC) and headless (Python API)
- New headless processing methods go in `utils/acloudviewer_backend.py`
- New GUI-only methods should use `self._rpc.call("method.name", params)`

## CLI Harness (Python Click)

- CLI commands are in `acloudviewer_cli.py` using Click groups
- All commands should use the `@handle_error` decorator
- Output goes through `output()` which respects `--json` flag
- Session mutations require `sess.snapshot("description")` before changes
- Command groups: `scene`, `view`, `process`, `session`

## Testing

- Unit tests in `tests/test_core.py` — no external dependencies
- E2E tests in `tests/test_full_e2e.py` — GUI tests gated by `ACLOUDVIEWER_E2E_GUI=1`
- Run tests: `pytest cli_anything/acloudviewer/tests/ -v`

